Package: RespiratoryDrugPathways
Type: Package
Title: A package to generate real-world treatment patterns for patients with asthma, COPD and asthma/COPD overlap
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Aniek F Markus 
Maintainer: Aniek F Markus <a.markus@erasmusmc.nl>
Description: This package gives insight in treatment patterns, the following tasks are performed sequentially:
    1. Target/outcome cohorts of interest are extracted from the database (defined using ATLAS or custom concept sets created in SQL inserted into cohort template) 
    2. Characterization of study/target population
    3. Treatment pathways are constructed
    4. Output is generated (sunburst plots and more)
    Go to extras -> CodeToRun.R to execute package
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.1),
    DatabaseConnector
Imports: 
    SqlRender,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    scales,
    gridExtra,
    data.table,
    stringr,
    glue,
    readr,
    networkD3,
    tidyr
